'From Squeak2.8alpha of 12 January 2000 [latest update: #1984] on 4 April 2000 at 2:55:58 pm'!"Change Set:		ProjectConversionDate:			4 April 2000Author:			Dan IngallsConversion methods needed when downloading content from old Projects and ChangeSets.  Note that ChangeSets will lose their contents.  Another update will follow with a more civilized solution."!!ChangeSet methodsFor: 'converting' stamp: 'di 4/4/2000 14:42'!convertcmcmnppss0: varDict nppriicss0: smartRefStrm	"These variables are automatically stored into the new instance ('name' 'preamble' 'postscript' 'structures' 'superclasses' ).	This method is for additional changes. Use statements like (foo _ varDict at: 'foo')."	"New variables: ('revertable' 'isolationSet' 'isolatedProject' 'changeRecords' )  If a non-nil value is needed, please assign it."	"These are going away ('classChanges' 'methodChanges' 'classRemoves' 'methodRemoves' ).  Possibly store their info in another variable?"	revertable _ false.	isolationSet _ nil.	isolatedProject _ nil.	changeRecords _ Dictionary new.	! !!Project methodsFor: 'object fileIn' stamp: 'di 4/4/2000 14:35'!convertdwctppdaevtngpiicmovue0: varDict dwctppdaevtngpiivue0: smartRefStrm	"These variables are automatically stored into the new instance ('world' 'changeSet' 'transcript' 'parentProject' 'previousProject' 'displayDepth' 'activeProcess' 'exitFlag' 'viewSize' 'thumbnail' 'nextProject' 'guards' 'projectParameters' 'isolatedHead' 'inForce' 'version' 'urlList' 'environment' ).	This method is for additional changes. Use statements like (foo _ varDict at: 'foo')."	isolatedHead _ false.	inForce _ false.! !